# Project Configuration

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| UI | React 19 |
| State | Zustand 5 (global) + TanStack Query 5 (server) |
| Language | TypeScript 6.0 strict |
| Bundler | Vite 8 (Rolldown + Oxc — official `vite` package) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS **v4** (CSS-based config — no tailwind.config.ts) |
| Components | shadcn/ui (new-york style) |
| Routing | React Router v7 |
| Forms | react-hook-form v7 + zod v4 |
| i18n | i18next 26 + react-i18next 17 |
| Testing | Vitest 4 + Testing Library |

## Tailwind v4 (CRITICAL)

**There is no `tailwind.config.ts`.** All config in `src/index.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "tw-animate-css";
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));

@theme inline {
  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  /* ... all tokens here */
}

:root { --primary: 221.2 83.2% 53.3%; }
.dark { --primary: 217.2 91.2% 59.8%; }
```

- Dark mode via `.dark` class (NOT `darkMode: 'class'` in JS config — that file doesn't exist).
- Animations via `tw-animate-css` package (CSS import, not a PostCSS plugin).
- `@tailwindcss/vite` handles compilation — do NOT add tailwindcss to PostCSS.
- Adding new color token: add HSL value to `:root`, map in `@theme inline`.

## i18n

- Translations in `public/locales/{lng}/{ns}.json`
- Namespaces: `common` (always loaded), `errors` (always loaded), page-specific (lazy), feature-specific (lazy on demand)
- Language detection: `localStorage` → browser → fallback `'en'`
- HMR: auto-reload translations in dev when files in `public/locales/` change
- No hardcoded user-visible strings — always use `t('key')`.

```typescript
const { t } = useTranslation(['common', 'home']);
return <h1>{t('home:title')}</h1>;
```

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML first: prefer `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>` over `<div role="...">`.
- ARIA only where semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Loading states: `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"`.
- Error states: `role="alert"` + `aria-live="assertive"`.
- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements must be keyboard-reachable.
- shadcn/ui components include accessibility by default — don't override without reason.

## Path Aliases

`@/` maps to `src/`. **Only use `@/` aliases — never relative `../../`.**

```typescript
import { useUserStore } from '@/store/user/userStore';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
```
